lm-festival-awards-1201693027/ |title=Sundance: ''The Birth of a Nation'' Sweeps Top Prizes |accessdate=1 February 2016 |work=Variety}}</ref>\n|[[Alfred P. Sloan Prize]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| [[Yerevan International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Awards and Juries|url=http://www.gaiff.am/en/winners|website=YEREVAN INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL|date=2015|access-date=18 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130118045655/http://www.gaiff.am/en/winners|archive-date=18 January 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| Golden Apricot Award\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[Riviera International Film Festival]]<ref name=\"Vogue Italia\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.it/en/news/daily-news/2017/05/01/riviera-international-film-festival/ |title=Riviera International Film Festival |accessdate=15 May 2017 |work=Vogue Italia}}</ref>\n|[[Grand Jury Prize]] for [[Best Picture]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| [[Jury Prize]] for Best Director\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Top ten lists===\nIn ''[[The Observer]]'' [[Mark Kermode]] included ''Embrace of the Serpent'' in his top ten list of best films of 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/dec/04/mark-kermode-best-films-2016-under-shadow-notes-on-blindness-room-son-saul |title=Mark Kermode: best films of 2016 |last=Kermode |first=Mark |authorlink=Mark Kermode |newspaper=[[The Observer]] |date=4 December 2016 |accessdate=15 February 2019}}</ref> ''Embrace of the Serpent'' is ranked 2nd in [[Rotten Tomatoes]]' ''Best-Reviewed Foreign Language Movies 2016'',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/best-foreign-language-movie-2016/ |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |title=Best-Reviewed Foreign Language Movies 2016}}</ref> and 23rd in the ''Top 100 Movies of 2016'' list.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/top/bestofrt/?year=2016 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |title=Top 100 Movies of 2016}}</ref> It also was named the 12th best film of 2016 by ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.esquire.com/entertainment/movies/a47757/best-movies-to-watch-2016/ |title=The 25 Best Movies of 2016 (So Far) |magazine=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] |last=Schager |first=Nick |date=30 November 2016}}</ref> ''[[Sight & Sound]]'' ranked it 21st with seven votes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/best-films-2016 |title=The best films of 2016 |publisher=British Film Institute |date=2 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nSome other top ten lists in which ''Embrace of the Serpent'' was listed are:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/feature/film-critics-list-the-top-10-movies-of-2016 |title=Best of 2016: Film Critic Top Ten Lists |publisher=Metacritic |last=Dietz |first=Jason |date=5 December 2016}}</ref>\n* 1st \u2013 J. R. Jones, ''[[Chicago Reader]]''\n* 2nd \u2013 ''[[Lincoln Journal Star]]''\n* 2nd \u2013 Randy Myers, ''[[San Jose Mercury News]]''\n* 3rd \u2013 ''[[Little White Lies (magazine)|Little White Lies]]''\n* 4th \u2013 [[Stephen Holden]], ''[[The New York Times]]''\n* 4th \u2013 ''[[The Irish Times]]''\n* 7th \u2013 ''[[Time Out London]]''\n* 8th \u2013 Brian Formo, ''[[Collider (website)|Collider]]''\n* 10th \u2013 Simon Abrams, ''[[RogerEbert.com]]''\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of submissions to the 88th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n*[[List of Colombian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|4285496|Embrace of the Serpent}}\n*{{Allmovie title|649344|Embrace of the Serpent}}\n*''[http://scienceandfilm.org/projects/534/embrace-of-the-serpent Embrace of the Serpent]'' at Science & Film\n{{Platino Award for Best Ibero-American Film}}\n{{Colombian submission for Academy Awards}}\n\n[[Category:2015 drama films]]\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:Alfred P. Sloan Prize winners]]\n[[Category:Colombian black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Colombian drama films]]\n[[Category:Colombian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Ciro 